CatDescriptText: Portion of related article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 9, 1941, pg. 3 reads: "James Weldon Johnson Camp Model Project - Above are scenes from Camp James Weldon Johnson, situated on Raccoon Creek in foothills of the beautiful Allegehney [Allegheny] mountains just 34 miles from Pittsburg [Pittsburgh]. Some of the children who enjoyed the facilities of the spacious grounds during the past two weeks are pictured...."
TitMainTitle: Man wearing dark belted bathing suit, standing on edge of diving board, preparing to dive into lake, at Camp Weldon Johnson, Beaver County, Pennsylvania
